Justice was finally served on Wednesday when the Tsomo Regional Magistrate's Court sentenced a 25-year-old man, Sithabile Gwicana, to 25 years behind bars for rape of a 15-year-old girl in December last year."The rape was committed on 22 December 2016, at about 24:00, at Komkhulu Location, in Thoboyi Village, Ngqamakhwe," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha."The victim met with the accused while they were at a traditional ceremony."He said that the victim was dragged to a dark area as it was midnight."She was raped by the accused. The Butterworth FCS Unit later traced and arrested the accused," Captain Manatha added."He was sentenced on Wednesday to undergo 25 years imprisonment."